        <td bgcolor="black" colspan="2"  valign="top">
		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;09/21/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 13:31:51</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=10016"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
 
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=10016')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&amp;TOPIC_ID=8730&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Post+60+Pets%2C+Items%2C+Spells+and+Skills%2E+%28Wishlist%29"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> Things I'd personally like to see are 4-fold. If not with the release of PoP, then sometime down the road.</P><P><b>Pets:</b></P><P>* Warrior Pet; insanely good hit point pool and AE-type taunt (or maybe innate single-target proc of Enraging blow instead.)? summoning ability?</P><P>* Rogue Pet; much improved backstab damage if given a piercing weapon? Maybe second reagent could be a tiny dagger? summoning ability? Evade type ability?</P><P>* Upgraded Monk Pet (missing); suggest level 64; summoning ability? ability to feign death when player does?</P><P>* Level 65 SK Pet; summoning ability? ability to cast it's own pet if handed a bone chip? :eek   ...ability to feign death when players does?</P><P>* All pets; improved damage:delay when given weapons which are better than their innate D:d? Would give us a choice of damage sort of... whether or not our Warrior used 2x 1HS or 2HS + Kick, and our SK using 1HS + Bash, or 2HS (i.e.- more damage at the expense of bash ability). Those changes raise questions for Monks and Rogues... wouldn't Monks be restricted to HTH, 1HB and 2HB? and wouldn't Rogues have to be handed piercing weapon(s) to BS... it's alot, sure, but one can always dream.</P><P>* Since Pet Resists work off player resists, how's about pets keeping up with us Run I, II and III? "pls SoW my pet" gets old...</P><P>* Someone suggested bringing back the old pet models; I'm all for that. The new ones suck... badly. They just fucking suck SO badly, that it makes me glad that my main character is a Monk. If those who like the newer ones are happy with the look, fine, but to me, 5 more levels of pets with the same animations (and lacks thereof) and "Beevis graphic" is intolerable.</P><P><b>Spells:</b></P><P>* Upgrade to Screaming Terror is a <b>must.</b> This Undead-Only stuff is a bad joke considering the lack of high-level undead-only zones, and the hodge-podge mixture of live/undead in zones like Howling Stones and Sebilis (heh- don't even get me started about Velious).</P><P>* Since alot of us solo and there's usually a mix of live/undead, how's about an upgrade to Numb the Dead which ISN'T undead only? Something like Lull, but reasonable AoE and Disease check instead of Magic. "Cloud of Weariness" or something...</P><P>* The last thing we need is more expensive snares with long-ass cast times.. hell, I'd rather see a pet-buff which imbues them with a snare proc' than another upgrade to Darkness (should be in our SK pet's spell repetoire anyways and go off like crazy- ala mage's Earth_ele).</P><P>* Upgrade to Splurt would be nice, same with FP; prop's to the Dev Team for NOT gimping us with Ancient Spells along those lines. Neither would make or break us if they weren't upgraded since there is a short list of "glaring holes" in our spellbooks; utility spells which would make up for our lack of travel spells, summoned items, and buffing ability.</P><P>* Group Quivering Veil of Xarn would be useful for Exp grouping, as well as certain raid-type situations if it would "stack" with (or at least not bounce off of) Bard DA song, or DA itself.</P><P>* _Group_Feign_Death_ anyone? See "Skills" below. This, imho, is a "must."</P><P>* 96% Componentless Ressurection at a greater mana cost/cast/recast; or Ess Em + better mana/cast/recast than Convergence. Necro's are the Masters of Death afterall, not any E-cleric with a click-stick. See Skills and Items below.</P><P>* PBAE or Targetable AE Nukes in three lines: One Poison with a Snare and/or DoT component, another Disease with a Stun and/or Debuff component, and Magic-based AE Drain Life/Mana Seive. Sure, most of us solo and these would be about useless for spawn-nursing solo artists, but not all of us do that, and, you may call it "AE envy" or whatever, but, other than Lifetaps, Necro's have always lacked a decent use for the Evocation skill, and lacked AE spells in general. I can see my Necro memming "Rain of Plague" or "Poison Torrent" or "Soul Seive."</P><P>* A *real* upgrade to Sedulous Subversion. For Cazic's sake, it's not as if we want to be PC-Mod-Rod's, but even with focus effects we're stuck at this 1:4 transfer ratio... how's about something that takes our HP and Mana and gives one or the other or both to another player at 2:3 ratio? We'd still be the worst healers and sources of mana in the game (AA skills like "Gather Mana" render this line almost obsolete anyway).</P><P>* Speaking of healing, we need a better "Renew Bones" type spell, but a dropped 1000hp:125m pet-heal spell is insane. I'm not complaining, really, but you could make Research mean something again with a 33% heal or something. Pet C-heal for 333 mana? heh~  1/2 of "666."</P><P>* The kicker- how about an NPC targetable spell like Sacrifice which poofs the mob (no_corpse), and yields no experience, but turns an Emerald into an Essence Emerald? Even if it's rather mana intensive, or has a long recast time of, like, 12 minutes or something...</P><P><b>Skills:</b></P><P>* Reuse time of Mend Companion is a too long. Honestly. It'd be worth 9 AA points if it could be used once per day. As it is, I'll never put points into it.. if my pet is that bad off, and I'm that LOM, I'll just FD.</P><P>* Make Lifeburn (Crit)-able. Again, with the 2-day timeouts. Sheesh.</P><P>* Pet Discipline is stupid. Very stupid. Too Stupid for words.</P><P>* Flesh to Bone. See above. "Hey, Can I have that Centi Meat?"</P><P>* I'd like to see a once per game day (or every-other game day) 100% resurrection ability for 9 AA points. Hello, E-clerics.</P><P>* If neither the 100 res, or Group FD Spell, how's about a once per day Group FD *skill* for 9 AA points? No need for mana; can activate it while oom, no chance of interruption or fizzle, and instantaneous (good for those laggy raids where you find yourself 5000 milliseconds back in time).</P><P>* Dodge is capped ridiculously low for all Casters (and priests)... think about bumping it up to 100 or more... it's not as if there are any "+50% Dodge" Skill-Mod items in the game either.</P><P><b>Items:</b></P><P>* How's about a +50% Dodge Skill Mod item for INT casters?  /grin, /jk</P><P>* Focus items: There are just too many things wrong with these, even if one doesn't compare the INT classes with each other, much less with priest classes and hybrids. For example, the 'Ring of Lighting' should've been Spell Haste III or something... if not Spell haste IV; Grat's Magicians, and the nifty little Gem Encrusted Ring Effect- "HEY, VERANT, SERVERS WHICH CAME OUT AFTER KUNARK NEVER GOT THESE RINGS." Grat's older servers who farmed Giants in DL for weeks before they nerfed the loot tables. Incidently, those servers are probably why NECKLACES OF SUPERIORITY only have that spell haste II effect. Yay~</P><P>* Necro Epic: mixed reaction already, not gonna touch it other than the reward is decent for the effort.. and it's unique graphic is, um... well... "unique." Focus Effect would be a nice addition though.</P><P>* Necro's have the hardest choices to make for spells, there are very few items which "free-up" spell slots, even at the highest end-game levels. If it was meant to be a penalty for being powerful, I suggest that we are at a slight imbalance with other classes. Pre-nerf CoS doesn't make up for it... there are some servers which will never have them (except via Legends exploitation). The FD mask-nerf is another peve along simliar lines. To be clear, I am not complaining about hard choices, only pointing out a perceivable under-itemization.</P><P>* Essence Emeralds.. what if they dropped as gem loot? Off of mobs such as Blood or Emperor in Seb?</P><P>...</P><P><BR>Ebonscar<BR>Tholuxe Paells</P><P><BR>Edited by - Ebonscar on 09/23/2002  02:28:26</font></td>

