         verant needs to completely rethink the way they work spell upgrades... its always been "higher level spell = higher mana cost, longer cast time, and does more damage" this doesnt have to be the case... in fact it would be more useful (especially with darkness) to have a higher level spell that does about the same damage (maybe slightly more) but has a shorter cast time. possibly make the mana cost higher if they feel its needed to balance out. i think its kind of silly though. making the spell higher level is a restriction in and of itself... they could make ALL spells available at level 1. would it break the game? umm... i dont think so. a level 1 character only has a very small mana pool... they might be able to use a spell thats a spell circle above what theyre at.. thatd be about it. but since the spells arent available at any level.. theres no need to make every spell hugely mana intensive just because its a higher level spell.</P><P>but then again class based games always were retarded. it'll be nice to see a real skill based game come out in the (hopefully) near future.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
